snippet: Israeli warplanes responded to rocket fire from Gaza on Monday by launching airstrikes, in a flare-up that began Sunday when Israel fired missiles against two suspected members of jihadist groups.
abstract: Israeli military says its jets hit rocket-launching squads in Gaza and sites belonging to Hamas; airstrikes come after militants fired rockets and shells into Israel.

byline.original: By ISABEL KERSHNER and FARES AKRAM
byline.contributor: Isabel Kershner reported from Jerusalem, and Fares Akram from Gaza.

lead_paragraph: Israeli warplanes responded to rocket fire from Gaza on Monday by launching airstrikes, in a flare-up that began Sunday when Israel fired missiles against two suspected members of jihadist groups.

headline.main: Israel Launches Airstrikes After Attacks From Gaza
headline.print_headline: Israel: Military Strikes in Gaza After Rocket Attacks
